    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="502"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d502">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Minister <persName type="to">Dawson</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 11, 1906</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 120.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    261, of the 16th ultimo, reporting on the Dominican-Haitian boundary
                    controversy.</p>
                <p>The intelligence and industry shown by you in the preparation of your report are
                    highly commended.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Robert Bacon.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
